  <chapter>
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <para><link xlink:href="http://www.eclipse.org/">Eclipse</link> is a
    multi-language software development environment with an extensible plugins
    system. <emphasis>Peergreen Server Eclipse plugin</emphasis> provides an
    efficient tool for developing OSGi applications within Eclipse IDE. With
    Peergreen Server plugin, developers are able to : <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
           launch Peergreen server from the IDE as an OSGi framework. 
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
           deploy the application bundle to test it. 
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
           retrieve new version of the server. 
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist></para>

    <para><note>
        <para>This tutorial was written with Eclipse Juno.</para>
      </note></para>
  </chapter>

  <chapter>
    <title>The application project</title>

    <para>We’re using the OSGi application example, named Hello Service,
    available <link
    xlink:href="https://github.com/peergreen/pax-exam/tree/master/hello-service">
    here</link>. The maven project defines a bundle which implements a single
    service Hello :</para>

    <programlisting language="java">package com.peergreen.example.ipojo.hello.api;

public interface Hello {
    String sayHello(String name);
}</programlisting>

    <para>The <literal>pom.xml</literal> includes : <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
           the maven bundle plugin to generate the OSGi bundle. 
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
           the maven ipojo plugin to enhance the classes with the IPOJO service management container. 
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist></para>

    <programlisting language="xml">&lt;build&gt;
  &lt;plugins&gt;
    &lt;plugin&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.felix&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-bundle-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;2.3.7&lt;/version&gt;
      &lt;extensions&gt;true&lt;/extensions&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;
    &lt;plugin&gt;
      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.felix&lt;/groupId&gt;
      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-ipojo-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
      &lt;version&gt;1.8.6&lt;/version&gt;
      &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
          &lt;goals&gt;
            &lt;goal&gt;ipojo-bundle&lt;/goal&gt;
          &lt;/goals&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
      &lt;/executions&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;
  &lt;/plugins&gt;
&lt;/build&gt;</programlisting>

